<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> demanded today that <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> not arrest a <LOCATION> Seoul </LOCATION> college student who violated a ban on visits to the communist north and now wants to return home, officials said today. <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> insisted that South Korean Prime Minister <PERSON> Kang </PERSON> <PERSON> Young-hoon </PERSON> give a public assurance that 20-year-old Im Su-kyong may return home as a free citizen through the border village of <LOCATION> Panmunjom </LOCATION>, officials said. `` If she is arrested and persecuted, North-South relations will be further aggravated, creating a grave obstacle in the road to peaceful unification,'' the message from <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> said. <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> said the message was relayed in a telephone call to South Korean Unification Minister <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Hong-koo </PERSON>. It was not immediately known whether <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> would allow Miss Im to cross the border. There have been few mutually acceptable crossings between the enemy nations since they were divided at the end of World War II. Park Jyun-kyu, chairman of <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>'s governing <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>, has warned that any North Korean attempt to send the student back to <LOCATION> Seoul </LOCATION> through <LOCATION> Panmunjom </LOCATION> `` will raise havoc on the present military status quo at the demarcation line.'' The Demilitarized Zone runs through the middle of the truce village. Also today, <ORGANIZATION> North </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Korean </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cross </ORGANIZATION> chief Son Song-pil se