<HEAD>Aerospace Giant Says Profit Up 11 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EL SEGUNDO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Rockwell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said that despite flat sales, its profit rose 11 percent to $ 178.1 million in the third quarter of its 1989 fiscal year compared with a year earlier. The aerospace, automotive, electronics and graphics firm reported earnings Wednesday of 70 cents a share for the period ended June 30. That compared with a profit of $ 214.7 million, or 82 cents a share, for the third quarter of 1988. The 1988 figure included a one-time favorable tax adjustment of $ 50.2 million. Sales for the 1989 third quarter were $ 3.2 billion, compared with $ 3.1 billion for the 1988 period. Profit for the first nine months of fiscal 1989 totaled $ 608.8 million, or $ 2.37 a share, compared with $ 626 million, or $ 2.34 a share, for the 1988 period. The fiscal 1989 earnings included $ 100 million from the sale of a division. Nine-month sales for 1989 were $ 9.2 billion, up from $ 8.8 billion in 1988.
