<HEAD>AT&amp;T Earnings Rise 18 Percent In Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telephone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telegraph </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>'s second-quarter profit grew 18 percent to a record $ 699 million, according to a statement Thursday that showed the company coping with intensifying competition in long-distance service Separately, <ORGANIZATION> Southwestern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said its earnings rose 22.8 percent in the quarter. <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T's sales of services _ primarily long-distance _ climbed 9.8 percent, while sales of products ranging from decorator phones to million-dollar switches rose 3.8 percent. `` It was an excellent quarter all around,'' <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> T </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Allen </PERSON> said in a news release. <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T achieved the record earnings in spite of strong gains made by its nearest rivals in long-distance. Earnings more than doubled in the latest quarter at both <ORGANIZATION> MCI </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telecommunications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, the majority owner of <ORGANIZATION> US </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sprint </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> T </ORGANIZATION> said its profit rose to $ 699 million, or 65 cents a share, from $ 594 million, or 55 cents a share, a year earlier Overall revenue from services, products and rentals rose 5.2 percent to $ 9.26 billion from $ 8.8 billion. For the first half, earnings rose 19.1 percent to $ 1.29 billion, or $ 1.20 a share, from $ 1.09 billion, or $ 1.01 a share, a year earlier. Revenue rose 4.2 percent to $ 17.9 billion from $ 17.2 billion. <ORGANIZATION> St. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Louis-based </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Southwestern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION>, one of <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T's offspring, said its earnings rose to $ 261.5 million, or 87 cents a share, from $ 212.9 million, or 71 cents a share, a year earlier. Revenue rose 5.3 percent to $ 2.14 billion from $ 2.03 billion. For the first half, <ORGANIZATION> Southwestern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION>'s profit rose 15.9 percent to $ 500.3 million, or $ 1.66 a share, from $ 431.6 million, or $ 1.44 a share. Revenue rose 4.1 percent to $ 4.2 billion from $ 4.03 billion.
