timism about where they -LRB- the talks -RRB- are going,'' <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> also dismissed a plan by <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> businessman <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Ritchie </PERSON> to buy <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> as a `` public relations attempt.'' <PERSON> Ritchie </PERSON>, who has been trying to buy Eastern in alliance with its unions, said Tuesday he is close to securing a `` highly confident'' letter from his financial adviser, <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION>. In the letter, <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> says it would agree to raise $ 280 million in debt financing for the Eastern bid, <PERSON> Ritchie </PERSON> told The Wall Street Journal. <PERSON> Ritchie </PERSON>, owner of a commodities trading firm, also said he has been talking with the <ORGANIZATION> AFL-CIO </ORGANIZATION> about an additional $ 200 million for an employee stock ownership plan.
